@startuml chess-coach-multiplayer-sequence
' SPEC: _spec/chess-coach/multiplayer-sequence.puml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml

actor "Player 1\n(host)" as W
participant "Host browser\n(room authority)" as Host
participant "Guest browser\n(player / observer)" as Guest
actor "Player 2" as B
participant "Observer browser\n(×0–4, optional)" as Obs

== Create room (host) ==
W -> Host: Create room + identity
Host -> Host: new RTCPeerConnection · createOffer\ngather ICE (non-trickle, iceServers:[])
Host -> W: render QR + link  (…/chess/lan#o=<sdp>)
note over Host: connection: Offering → AwaitingAnswer\nroom: Lobby (host seated, no color yet)

== Join (manual, out-of-band signaling) ==
note over W, B: share the offer QR/link out-of-band (show screen / message)
B -> Guest: open #o= link · enter identity · join as player
Guest -> Guest: setRemote(offer) · createAnswer\ngather ICE (non-trickle)
Guest -> B: render QR + link  (…/chess/lan#a=<sdp>)
note over W, B: Player 2 returns the answer QR/link out-of-band
W -> Host: scan / paste answer
Host -> Host: setRemote(answer) → RTCDataChannel opens
Guest -> Host: Hello { identity, desiredRole: player }
Host -> Host: add as player, no color yet\n(else observer ≤4 / else ROOM_FULL)
Host -> Guest: RoomState broadcast
Host -> Obs: RoomState broadcast (to all connected peers)
note over Host: connection: Connected · room: Lobby

== Add observer (optional, repeat ≤4) ==
note over Host, Obs: host taps "Add player" → fresh offer QR; same\noffer→answer exchange. Host assigns observer or replies ROOM_FULL.

== Color selection & swap (lobby) ==
W -> Host: ClaimColor { white }
B -> Guest: select a color seat (e.g. Black)
Guest -> Host: ClaimColor { black }
Host -> Host: validate distinct colors · update seats · reset ready votes
Host -> Guest: RoomState { players, colors }
Host -> Obs: RoomState broadcast
note over W, B: selecting the opposite (occupied) seat → SwapColor:\nhost exchanges both players' colors. ANY color change\nresets both ready votes (colors lock only at Start).

== Start gate (both players agree on colors; observers optional) ==
W -> Host: StartRequest { ready: true }
B -> Guest: press Start Game
Guest -> Host: StartRequest { ready: true }
Host -> Host: 2 players · distinct colors · both ready → started = true
Host -> Guest: RoomState { started: true }
Host -> Obs: RoomState { started: true }
note over Host, Obs: boards unlock for players; observers stay read-only.\nchanging a color after Start clears that ready vote

== Move relay (guest player to move — host is authoritative) ==
B -> Guest: drag piece (legal · their turn · own chosen color)
Guest -> Guest: addMove → lastHumanMoveInfo\n(aiOpponent=F → no AI turn)
Guest -> Host: Move { san }
Host -> Host: authoritative addMoveSan → new FEN
Host -> Guest: MoveApplied { san, fen }  (echo / confirm)
Host -> Obs: MoveApplied broadcast
note over Host: the host's own move applies locally first,\nthen the host broadcasts MoveApplied the same way

== Resign / disconnect / game over ==
B -> Guest: Resign
Guest -> Host: Resign { color: black }
Host -> Host: end game → gameOver
Host -> Guest: RoomState { gameOver }
Host -> Obs: RoomState { gameOver }

== Draw offer (host-authoritative; mirrored via RoomState.draw) ==
B -> Guest: tap Draw (no offer yet)
Guest -> Host: DrawOffer
Host -> Host: draw = { by: black, status: pending }
Host -> Guest: RoomState { draw }  (🤝 floats on black's king)
Host -> Obs: RoomState { draw }
note over W, B: a pending offer PERSISTS across moves until answered.\nthe offerer may DrawCancel (→ draw = null) while waiting.
W -> Host: tap 🤝 / Draw → "Accept Draw?"
alt White accepts
  W -> Host: DrawAccept
  Host -> Host: gameOver { draw, "Draw by agreement." } · draw = null
  Host -> Guest: RoomState { gameOver }
  Host -> Obs: RoomState { gameOver }
else White declines
  W -> Host: DrawDecline
  Host -> Host: draw = { by: black, status: declined }  (⚔️ on white's king)
  Host -> Guest: RoomState { draw }  (both 🤝 + ⚔️ shown)
  note over Host: next move by either side → clearResolvedDrawOnMove\n→ draw = null → both bubbles animate out
end

== Time control (host-authoritative clocks) ==
note over W, B: at creation the host picks a per-player clock (default from the\nlast Selena difficulty: Int=10m·Adv=5m·Exp=3m). It rides the\noffer link (tc=<sec>) so the joiner sees it before connecting.
Host -> Host: on start: clocks = { w, b } = tc·1000 ms · turnStartAt = now
note over Host: only the side-to-move's clock drains. On each move the host\ndeducts the mover's elapsed, hands the clock over, and ships\nclocks in MoveApplied (+ RoomState). Each peer ticks locally.
alt a clock reaches 0 (host's 250ms watch)
  Host -> Host: gameOver { winner = opponent, "<Loser> ran out of time." }
  Host -> Guest: RoomState { gameOver, clocks }
  Host -> Obs: RoomState { gameOver }
end

== Drop & reconnect (recoverable) ==
note over Guest: phone backgrounds → RTCPeerConnection "disconnected"/"failed"
Guest -> Guest: connectionStatus = connecting ("reconnecting…")
note over Host: peer "disconnected" (recoverable, NOT terminal):\nhold the seat, start a 15s grace timer, status = connecting
alt page returns within grace (ICE re-validates the 100.x path;\nrestartIce() nudged on visibilitychange)
  Guest -> Host: RTCPeerConnection "connected"
  Host -> Guest: RoomState { latest fen } (resync)
  Host -> Host: clear grace timer, status = connected
else grace expires (or terminal "closed")
  Host -> Host: dropPeer → gameOver { "Opponent disconnected." }
  Host -> Obs: RoomState { gameOver }
end
note over Host, Obs: host drop → all channels close → room ends (host is the authority).\nFull-background reconnect still needs a persistent signaling path (manual QR can't auto-re-exchange SDP).

@enduml
